value.value: The sulcus that arises medially from the ventral margin of the median ocellus and extends towards the intertorular carina.
The band that is transverse and composed of setae in Apoidea.
The setiferous patch that is located sublaterally on an abdominal sternum.
The band that is composed of flattened setae and secretory pores and is located laterally on abdominal tergum 3.
The genitalia that is part of the female organism.
The scrobe that is located on the mesopleuron into which the mesofemur fits when pressed against the mesosoma.
The leg segment that is distal to the trochanter and proximal to the tibia.
The sclerite that is located in the proximal end of the unpaired part of the ductus ejaculatorius.
The abdominal spiracle that is the anteriormost in the body.
The axillary sclerite that articulates with the mesonotum.
The sclerite that is located between the second axillary and the distal arm of the third axillary at the base of the mediocubital field.
The mesonotal muscle that arises ventrally from the mesopectus and inserts on the mesoscutum laterally of the notauli and medially of the parascutal carina.
The postoccipital muscle that originates from the first phragma and inserts on the postocciput.
The propleural muscle that arises medially from the prophragma and inserts on the posterodorsal margin of the propleuron.
The mesophragmal muscle that extends between the prophragma and mesophragma.
The gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle that inserts on the median wall of the harpe and arises distally of the site of origin of the proximal gonostyle/volsella complex-harpal muscle.
The wing cell that is located on the wing.

The area of the first valvifer-first valvula complex that is proximal to the aulax, bears the ninth tergal condyle of the first valvifer and the second valviferal condyle of the first valvifer and is connected to the genital membrane by muscle.
The area of the first valvifer-first valvula complex that is delimited distally by the proximal margin of the aulax.
The line that secondarily divides a sclerite.
The sclerite that is located at the apex of the glossa in Apoidea.
The annulus that is located distally of the pedicel.
The anatomical cluster composed of flagellomeres.
The projection that is lamella-like and is located on a rim, carina, apodeme or edge.
The anatomical space that is surrounded by sclerites and allows for the passage of haemolymph, nerves and tracheae.
The anatomical space that is surrounded by the proximal margin of the cupula.
The foramen that is delimited dorsally by the postocciput.
The leg that is located on the prothorax.
The tibia that is located on the fore leg.
The wing that is located on the mesothorax.
The articular surface that is concave and accommodates the condyle of another sclerite.
The line that is transverse, arched anteriorly and is continuous with the posterior margins of the mesoscutellar arms.
The area that is located posteriorly on the mesoscutellum and is delimited anteriorly by the frenal line.
The line that is median and extending on the frons.
The area that extends along the lateral margin of the upper face.
The setiferous patch that is located on the frons.
The suture that diverges ventrally (or anteriorly) from the coronal suture between the antennal foramina toward the anterior articulations of the mandibles.
The anatomical space that is delimited posteriorly by the distal part of the sitophore and anteriorly by the tormae.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of flagellomeres located between the pedicel and clava or the distalmost anellus and clava.
The annulus that is located in the funicle.
The apodeme that arises medially from the ventral part of the thorax and corresponds to the site of origin of interfurcal and coxal muscles.
The furca that is paired, arises medioventrally from the sternum and corresponds to the furcal pit.
The pit that corresponds to the furca.
The area that is located posteriorly on the prosternum and bears the profurca.
The lobe that is located on the stipes at the distal part of the posterior stipital sclerite distolateral to the lacinia.
The anatomical cluster that is composed of all abdominal segments posterior to abdominal segment 2.
The area that is concave, transverse, and located anterolaterally on abdominal tergum 3.
The area that is delimited by the intersection of the interorbital plane, the margin of the compound eye, the margin of the oral foramen, the occipital carina and the malar sulcus.
The setiferous patch that is located on the gena.
The anatomical system that is involved in copulation, fertilization and/or oviposition.
